1
00:00:00,610 --> 00:00:03,650
It's the battle part of day 
four of the Grand Magic Games!

2
00:00:03,650 --> 00:00:06,510
Due to the disqualification of Raven Tail,

3
00:00:06,730 --> 00:00:10,440
Fairy Tail's A and B teams have merged 
and are now in a tag team battle!

4
00:00:10,440 --> 00:00:12,780
Their opponents are Sabertooth!

5
00:00:12,780 --> 00:00:16,950
It's a dream showdown between 
four Dragon Slayers!

6
00:00:16,950 --> 00:00:20,000
Who will win, Fairy or Tiger?!

7
00:01:50,830 --> 00:01:53,800
Wh-What's this?!

8
00:01:53,800 --> 00:01:55,620
Sting and Rogue...

9
00:01:55,620 --> 00:01:59,340
The Twin Dragons of Fiore's 
strongest guild are on the ropes!

10
00:02:00,510 --> 00:02:03,840
He really is strong... But I'd 
be disappointed otherwise.

11
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:04,850
Gajeel...

12
00:02:05,340 --> 00:02:09,850
Did you two really defeat 
dragons with power like that?

13
00:02:09,850 --> 00:02:11,630
Not defeat...

14
00:02:12,220 --> 00:02:14,650
I killed a dragon with this very hand.

15
00:02:15,190 --> 00:02:17,620
Wasn't it your parent?

16
00:02:17,620 --> 00:02:19,920
It's got nothin' to do with you.

17
00:02:20,220 --> 00:02:23,620
From now, I'm gonna show you 
the power that killed a dragon!

18
00:02:24,610 --> 00:02:26,670
White Drive...

19
00:02:28,830 --> 00:02:30,800
Shadow Drive.

20
00:02:39,190 --> 00:02:43,460
Sting and Rogue, the Twin 
Dragons of Sabertooth...

21
00:02:43,710 --> 00:02:47,000
Dragon Slayers, like Natsu and Gajeel...

22
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:49,990
But their magic is still an unknown...

23
00:02:49,990 --> 00:02:53,170
Well, let's see what happens...

24
00:02:53,170 --> 00:02:56,540
I think they're done testing each other.

25
00:02:56,540 --> 00:03:00,210
From here on in, they're going to get 
serious, so let's really cheer them on!

26
00:03:00,750 --> 00:03:03,240
It's over, garbage guild.

27
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:04,990
Sting...

28
00:03:04,990 --> 00:03:06,240
Yeah...

29
00:03:06,490 --> 00:03:10,060
Alright, the silent face-off continues...

30
00:03:10,060 --> 00:03:13,960
...but the entire arena 
is filled with tension.

31
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:16,540
Which side will make the first move?!

32
00:03:20,480 --> 00:03:23,000
Sabertooth's Sting makes his move!

33
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:25,850
Fairy Tail's Natsu held it back!

34
00:03:26,240 --> 00:03:30,060
Receive Holy White Judgment!

35
00:03:31,570 --> 00:03:32,900
Salamander!

36
00:03:38,440 --> 00:03:44,700
Oh, my! It looks like Fairy Tail's Gajeel 
is at the mercy of Rogue's Shadow Drive!

37
00:03:44,930 --> 00:03:47,620
You can't get ahold of shadows.

38
00:03:50,380 --> 00:03:51,910
Take this!

39
00:03:57,070 --> 00:03:58,790
Don't get in my way!

40
00:04:00,330 --> 00:04:03,630
Squabbling in the middle of a match?! 
You guys sure have confidence!

41
00:04:06,510 --> 00:04:08,760
Their power has suddenly increased.

42
00:04:08,760 --> 00:04:11,290
Is that a kind of Dragon Slayer Magic?

43
00:04:11,290 --> 00:04:14,180
Take care of business, Natsu!

44
00:04:14,180 --> 00:04:17,270
What the hell?! You've gotten 
faster for some reason...

45
00:04:17,270 --> 00:04:21,150
Come on, come on, Natsu-san! 
You call that defense?!

46
00:04:25,440 --> 00:04:27,500
What on Earthland...?

47
00:04:27,500 --> 00:04:29,640
It's a magic amplification technique.

48
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:32,870
On top of that, their combination 
skills are seamless.

49
00:04:33,670 --> 00:04:36,090
This isn't as thrilling as I thought it'd be.

50
00:04:36,090 --> 00:04:41,590
Compared to those two, it seems Fairy 
Tail's duo aren't in sync with each other.

51
00:04:42,170 --> 00:04:46,310
Go! You're in your assured victory pattern!

52
00:04:46,310 --> 00:04:48,720
Fro thinks so, too!

53
00:04:51,210 --> 00:04:53,400
Four Dragons!

54
00:04:55,630 --> 00:04:57,730
Sabertooth!

55
00:05:03,760 --> 00:05:06,630
The tone of the crowd's cheering has changed.

56
00:05:06,630 --> 00:05:08,620
Natsu-san and Gajeel-san...

57
00:05:08,970 --> 00:05:11,060
...may be in trouble.

58
00:05:11,060 --> 00:05:15,170
It's only just begun. There's 
no need to be so anxious.

59
00:05:17,020 --> 00:05:20,360
I admired you for the longest time!

60
00:05:21,610 --> 00:05:25,210
And then I set my sights on surpassing you!

61
00:05:25,210 --> 00:05:28,410
Now is that time!

62
00:05:28,410 --> 00:05:29,450
Natsu!

63
00:05:29,740 --> 00:05:31,450
That attack just now...

64
00:05:31,450 --> 00:05:34,630
There's something different about 
it compared to previous attacks.

65
00:05:35,490 --> 00:05:36,980
What do you mean?

66
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:40,860
And what the hell is that?! It 
looks like a Magic Circle...

67
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:46,010
C-Can't...

68
00:05:46,010 --> 00:05:47,890
...move!

69
00:05:47,890 --> 00:05:50,990
The Claw of the White 
Dragon is a holy attack.

70
00:05:51,470 --> 00:05:55,060
A body that's marked by its 
stigmata loses its freedom.

71
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:59,580
And with this, I'll surpass you!

72
00:06:04,650 --> 00:06:07,870
The dragon that becomes 
shadow hides its form.

73
00:06:09,070 --> 00:06:11,550
It always takes down its prey!

74
00:06:13,150 --> 00:06:15,520
It always takes down...

75
00:06:16,370 --> 00:06:18,210
What is it?

76
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:20,030
Yeah!

77
00:06:20,030 --> 00:06:21,960
That's the way, Gajeel!

78
00:06:21,960 --> 00:06:25,610
He caught him! Even though before, 
he wasn't even able to land a hit!

79
00:06:25,610 --> 00:06:30,360
Of course! After fighting for a 
while, Gajeel gets used to it.

80
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:32,770
Natsu can do the same thing with ease!

81
00:06:32,770 --> 00:06:35,250
Get 'im, Natsu!

82
00:06:42,760 --> 00:06:44,500
How can you move?!

83
00:06:46,980 --> 00:06:49,170
You burned off the stigmata!

84
00:06:49,630 --> 00:06:51,890
Not too shabby...

85
00:06:52,340 --> 00:06:54,140
But you've got a ways to go.

86
00:06:55,380 --> 00:06:59,210
He burned it off... That 
guy knows no bounds...

87
00:06:59,210 --> 00:07:02,100
"Only the Salamander could do 
that..." I guess I should say...

88
00:07:02,350 --> 00:07:05,330
Don't get too stuck on yourselves, brats.

89
00:07:06,950 --> 00:07:08,900
And don't make light of Fairy Tail!

90
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:14,400
Just like that! Go! Go!

91
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:16,310
That was great, Gajeel!

92
00:07:16,310 --> 00:07:19,200
I-I can't breathe... Calm down, Levy!

93
00:07:20,530 --> 00:07:25,210
Oh, my! The course of the 
battle has just shifted again!

94
00:07:26,190 --> 00:07:29,440
You guys really are the best.

95
00:07:32,630 --> 00:07:35,720
We have to give this our all and then some.

96
00:07:36,710 --> 00:07:41,600
The Fist of the White Dragon even 
reduces flames to smithereens.

97
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:45,140
What is that magic?! The 
pressure is incredible!

98
00:07:45,140 --> 00:07:47,690
I don't like this... I think it might be...

99
00:07:47,690 --> 00:07:51,480
S-So bright! Yajima-san, what is this?!

100
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:56,490
Sting-kun is concentrating his 
magic into a single point.

101
00:07:56,890 --> 00:07:59,160
Here I go, Natsu-san!

102
00:07:59,580 --> 00:08:01,480
Dragon Slayer Arcana!

103
00:08:01,480 --> 00:08:04,670
Holy Nova!

104
00:08:23,220 --> 00:08:25,920
Whoa! What's this?!

105
00:08:25,920 --> 00:08:30,480
He stopped that tremendous 
attack with one hand!

106
00:08:31,330 --> 00:08:33,670
I-I don't believe it...

107
00:08:33,670 --> 00:08:34,740
Huh?

108
00:08:37,140 --> 00:08:38,360
No way...

109
00:08:38,360 --> 00:08:41,410
I have no memory of that 
skill ever being blocked.

110
00:08:41,830 --> 00:08:43,630
I see...

111
00:08:43,930 --> 00:08:47,580
Now it makes sense why he would 
storm into our inn on his own.

112
00:08:47,870 --> 00:08:52,550
I wonder what I could have seen 
if I hadn't stopped him then...

113
00:08:53,460 --> 00:08:55,330
Sting-kun...

114
00:08:55,330 --> 00:08:57,800
Yajima-san, what do you make of this?!

115
00:08:57,800 --> 00:08:59,500
Gajeel!

116
00:09:06,500 --> 00:09:08,060
Rogue...

117
00:09:10,850 --> 00:09:14,070
So three months of training and Second Origin

118
00:09:14,650 --> 00:09:17,530
made these two this strong, eh?

119
00:09:20,570 --> 00:09:22,870
They belong to totally different ranks.

120
00:09:29,470 --> 00:09:31,440
Even I can pick up on it.

121
00:09:31,440 --> 00:09:34,140
The way they're cheering 
has changed again, right?

122
00:09:34,140 --> 00:09:35,220
Yes.

123
00:09:37,090 --> 00:09:38,920
Lucy, you were awake?

124
00:09:38,920 --> 00:09:41,940
Yeah. I just can't sleep.

125
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:46,170
Natsu and Gajeel will win, won't they?

126
00:09:47,380 --> 00:09:52,100
Wh-Who could have foreseen this development?!

127
00:09:52,100 --> 00:09:57,200
The Twin Dragons of Sabertooth, 
helpless before Fairy Tail!

128
00:09:57,530 --> 00:10:00,780
Will the match end like this?!

129
00:10:03,290 --> 00:10:05,220
Like hell it'll end...

130
00:10:05,220 --> 00:10:06,510
Yeah...

131
00:10:06,510 --> 00:10:10,130
I knew this wasn't gonna be 
an easy wall to get over...

132
00:10:16,750 --> 00:10:18,260
Sting-kun...

133
00:10:19,270 --> 00:10:22,380
I know, Lector...

134
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:27,300
We made a promise, right?

135
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:34,590
I'm not gonna lose.

136
00:10:40,290 --> 00:10:42,380
I can't lose...

137
00:10:42,750 --> 00:10:44,480
For Lector's sake...

138
00:10:47,580 --> 00:10:50,400
What the hell is this magic?!

139
00:10:50,670 --> 00:10:51,790
They're...

140
00:10:52,040 --> 00:10:54,330
Wh-What is this...?

141
00:10:54,670 --> 00:10:58,610
Tremble at the true power 
of the Third Generation.

142
00:10:58,610 --> 00:11:02,640
Impossible! They can activate 
it with their own will?!

143
00:11:03,510 --> 00:11:05,200
Dragon Force...

144
00:11:05,790 --> 00:11:09,400
Natsu kinda looked like that 
at the Tower of Heaven...

145
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:11,520
Yeah. Except...

146
00:11:12,310 --> 00:11:16,360
...he gained the power 
then by eating Etherion.

147
00:11:16,810 --> 00:11:22,030
And that time with Zero too, he unleashed 
that power by eating all of my magic.

148
00:11:22,860 --> 00:11:27,630
But they're able to release the 
power of the Dragon by willing it?!

149
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:34,630
This is the Third Generation 
of Dragon Slayers.

150
00:11:35,260 --> 00:11:37,330
Rogue, hang back.

151
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:42,550
I can take both of them on by myself.

152
00:11:58,960 --> 00:12:03,200
U-Until just a minute ago, 
Sabertooth was being dominated!

153
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:05,570
Unbelievably, he's challenged both of them!

154
00:12:06,020 --> 00:12:09,020
That's how much confidence he has, huh?

155
00:12:09,020 --> 00:12:10,630
That's right!

156
00:12:10,630 --> 00:12:14,240
Sting-kun and Rogue-kun have Dragon Force.

157
00:12:14,530 --> 00:12:16,520
There's no way they can lose!

158
00:12:16,520 --> 00:12:18,640
I was worried for nothing!

159
00:12:19,070 --> 00:12:22,340
Fro forgot about Dragon Force, too!

160
00:12:22,900 --> 00:12:26,790
I haven't seen it yet, but 
is it really all that?

161
00:12:27,030 --> 00:12:29,750
Yeah. At this rate, the 
odds are against them.

162
00:12:30,680 --> 00:12:32,360
It's gotten quiet...

163
00:12:32,810 --> 00:12:34,310
Maybe they're finished?

164
00:12:34,310 --> 00:12:36,480
No. It begins here...

165
00:12:36,750 --> 00:12:38,340
Shall I check it out?

166
00:12:38,340 --> 00:12:40,890
No, you don't have to.

167
00:12:41,560 --> 00:12:44,250
I'm sure Natsu and Gajeel will be fine.

168
00:12:51,360 --> 00:12:52,990
They're lookin' down on us...

169
00:12:53,550 --> 00:12:55,200
But this feeling...

170
00:12:55,940 --> 00:12:57,230
He's strong.

171
00:13:15,050 --> 00:13:16,370
I-It's different...

172
00:13:16,370 --> 00:13:18,280
Totally different from before!

173
00:13:18,280 --> 00:13:19,190
Natsu-nii...

174
00:13:26,430 --> 00:13:30,200
Holy Breath of the White Dragon!

175
00:13:36,530 --> 00:13:38,040
W-What is it?!

176
00:13:38,040 --> 00:13:40,540
We can feel the magic at this distance?!

177
00:13:41,630 --> 00:13:44,560
That's because it's a battle 
between Dragon Slayers.

178
00:13:44,950 --> 00:13:46,630
The cost is going to be heavy.

179
00:13:47,830 --> 00:13:48,770
Natsu...

180
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:50,350
Gajeel...

181
00:13:55,020 --> 00:13:58,300
Oh, dear! What is going on here?!

182
00:13:58,300 --> 00:14:00,180
The floor of the arena is...

183
00:14:00,760 --> 00:14:02,220
...crumbling?!

184
00:14:02,220 --> 00:14:04,900
That was one fierce breath...

185
00:14:05,440 --> 00:14:07,220
What incredible force...

186
00:14:07,610 --> 00:14:12,100
Is this the power of the Third 
Generation Dragon Slayers?!

187
00:14:12,750 --> 00:14:13,950
Gajeel!

188
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:16,030
Natsu!

189
00:14:16,610 --> 00:14:20,060
It seems the battlefield is 
moving underneath the arena,

190
00:14:20,060 --> 00:14:21,920
but the match will continue!

191
00:14:22,690 --> 00:14:26,240
Everyone, please enjoy it on Lacrima-Vision!

192
00:14:27,960 --> 00:14:30,290
I'm just getting started!

193
00:14:34,260 --> 00:14:38,590
Sword Horn of the Fire Dragon!

194
00:14:39,890 --> 00:14:43,940
Roar of the Iron Dragon!

195
00:14:53,160 --> 00:14:57,790
The light of the White Dragon 
purifies all things...

196
00:14:58,940 --> 00:15:00,760
Holy Ray!

197
00:15:06,780 --> 00:15:07,960
Light?!

198
00:15:08,710 --> 00:15:10,970
Holy attribute magic...

199
00:15:21,420 --> 00:15:22,610
Fly.

200
00:15:25,150 --> 00:15:28,060
Natsu can't guard against him?!

201
00:15:28,060 --> 00:15:30,570
What happened to that confident 
mood from just before?!

202
00:15:48,130 --> 00:15:51,230
Sting-kun really is strong, huh?

203
00:15:51,230 --> 00:15:53,470
Fro thinks so, too!

204
00:15:54,150 --> 00:15:57,510
Lector... I made you a promise...

205
00:15:59,350 --> 00:16:01,430
...so I'm definitely gonna win!

206
00:16:10,810 --> 00:16:13,400
Were you bullied again, Lector?

207
00:16:14,220 --> 00:16:17,910
After all... nobody believes me!

208
00:16:18,690 --> 00:16:21,880
I told them you beat a dragon, Sting-kun!

209
00:16:21,880 --> 00:16:25,350
I'm not lying about it!

210
00:16:26,380 --> 00:16:28,450
I know.

211
00:16:28,450 --> 00:16:30,780
Never mind jerks like that.

212
00:16:30,780 --> 00:16:34,680
I can't! They were saying bad 
things about you, Sting-kun!

213
00:16:35,440 --> 00:16:37,320
I don't care.

214
00:16:37,720 --> 00:16:40,850
I... I...

215
00:16:41,170 --> 00:16:44,510
I hate it when people say 
bad things about my friend!

216
00:16:48,290 --> 00:16:49,820
Okay.

217
00:16:50,120 --> 00:16:53,150
Then I'll prove you're not a liar.

218
00:16:56,100 --> 00:17:01,010
There may not be any more dragons, but there 
is somebody called "Salamander", right?

219
00:17:02,630 --> 00:17:06,960
One day, I'll beat him, 
right in front of everybody.

220
00:17:08,180 --> 00:17:09,680
I promise.

221
00:17:26,080 --> 00:17:28,710
Are you watching this, Lector?!

222
00:17:29,920 --> 00:17:32,720
I'm watching, Sting-kun!

223
00:17:35,510 --> 00:17:38,280
It's become quiet again...

224
00:17:38,610 --> 00:17:41,390
Could those tremors from before mean...?

225
00:17:42,400 --> 00:17:45,580
It's alright. I mean, it's <i>those two</i>...

226
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:48,750
Right?

227
00:17:49,110 --> 00:17:51,780
Natsu... Gajeel...

228
00:17:53,550 --> 00:17:55,750
Times change.

229
00:17:56,610 --> 00:18:02,640
The span of seven years has allowed us 
to develop into true Dragon Slayers.

230
00:18:03,090 --> 00:18:05,700
The time of the old generation is over.

231
00:18:07,560 --> 00:18:08,720
Yeah.

232
00:18:09,590 --> 00:18:13,330
Uh-oh! They're not even twitching!

233
00:18:13,330 --> 00:18:16,500
It's been a breathless seesaw battle,

234
00:18:16,500 --> 00:18:20,630
but has Fairy Tail finally run out of steam?!

235
00:18:20,630 --> 00:18:22,030
Natsu...

236
00:18:22,410 --> 00:18:23,790
Gajeel...

237
00:18:23,790 --> 00:18:25,270
What's wrong?! Get up!

238
00:18:25,700 --> 00:18:27,910
You're stronger than this!

239
00:18:28,120 --> 00:18:30,560
Even Natsu and Gajeel can't beat them?!

240
00:18:30,560 --> 00:18:33,160
Damn, this sticks in my craw...

241
00:18:33,510 --> 00:18:37,060
Natsu-nii! Stand up!

242
00:18:39,310 --> 00:18:42,850
But you really were strong,

243
00:18:42,850 --> 00:18:45,440
Natsu-san... Gajeel-san...

244
00:18:46,350 --> 00:18:48,700
Are both of them down?!

245
00:18:49,220 --> 00:18:51,950
Stand up, Natsu! Gajeel!

246
00:18:51,950 --> 00:18:54,310
You can hear our voices, can't you?!

247
00:18:54,630 --> 00:18:58,450
The guild's thoughts are one!

248
00:18:59,870 --> 00:19:02,700
They're one with you!

249
00:19:03,090 --> 00:19:04,270
Sting!

250
00:19:04,270 --> 00:19:08,600
Yeah... Sorry I took Gajeel-san down, too.

251
00:19:09,160 --> 00:19:10,280
But, y'know...

252
00:19:10,800 --> 00:19:13,670
...I kept my promise.

253
00:19:14,070 --> 00:19:15,960
Don't be too hasty...

254
00:19:19,470 --> 00:19:22,020
Fairy Tail!

255
00:19:26,950 --> 00:19:29,820
Lucy-san! It feels like...

256
00:19:29,820 --> 00:19:34,550
That's them, alright. No matter how many 
times they fall, they always get up again.

257
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:37,690
I don't know if that should 
be called tough or stubborn...

258
00:19:37,690 --> 00:19:39,920
Awesome! I knew they could do it!

259
00:19:39,920 --> 00:19:43,050
Look at that, Levy! Our voices reached 'em!

260
00:19:43,050 --> 00:19:45,240
They're standing!

261
00:19:45,240 --> 00:19:47,740
We'd be in a bind if they weren't.

262
00:19:48,660 --> 00:19:50,460
Ow...

263
00:19:50,460 --> 00:19:52,070
You're better than I thought.

264
00:19:52,070 --> 00:19:54,830
Incredibly, they're alive and kicking!

265
00:19:55,700 --> 00:19:59,090
But I saw through all of your habits.

266
00:19:59,090 --> 00:20:00,100
What?!

267
00:20:01,720 --> 00:20:04,400
No way... It can't be...

268
00:20:04,400 --> 00:20:07,750
This is a bad dream...

269
00:20:08,100 --> 00:20:10,810
Fro thinks so, too...

270
00:20:11,300 --> 00:20:15,300
Your attack timing... Your 
posture when you defend...

271
00:20:15,300 --> 00:20:17,190
Even the rhythm of your breathing...

272
00:20:17,520 --> 00:20:18,900
What?!

273
00:20:18,900 --> 00:20:22,780
That's ridiculous! I'm using Dragon Force!

274
00:20:22,780 --> 00:20:27,260
Yeah, and it packs a wallop! 
My body aches all over, dammit!

275
00:20:27,260 --> 00:20:29,880
Don't get rattled, Sting. He's bluffing.

276
00:20:30,910 --> 00:20:32,120
Bluffin', you say?

277
00:20:32,120 --> 00:20:35,680
You really think the Salamander can pull 
off a trick that requires usin' his brain?!

278
00:20:35,680 --> 00:20:37,530
Oh, shut up!

279
00:20:38,080 --> 00:20:42,140
For example, when you attack, 
your pivot foot is facing 11:00.

280
00:20:42,140 --> 00:20:44,040
Nah, it's 10:00.

281
00:20:44,040 --> 00:20:45,380
It's 11:00!

282
00:20:45,930 --> 00:20:50,040
I could let you slide with 
10:30, but not 11:00!

283
00:20:50,040 --> 00:20:53,020
I say it's 11:00! 23:00 is fine, too!

284
00:20:53,020 --> 00:20:55,020
That's going around 360 degrees!

285
00:20:59,560 --> 00:21:03,090
What are those two fools doing?!

286
00:21:03,090 --> 00:21:07,540
They've got energy to spare. And that means 
they've still got fight left in them.

287
00:21:07,850 --> 00:21:10,220
Arguing at a time like this...

288
00:21:10,220 --> 00:21:13,600
Yeesh, they make me wanna crawl in a hole...

289
00:21:13,600 --> 00:21:18,130
Oh, don't be like that. You 
and Natsu are two of a kind.

290
00:21:18,570 --> 00:21:21,160
When you look at me objectively, 
that's what you see?

291
00:21:21,160 --> 00:21:22,840
Clam it, already!

292
00:21:23,840 --> 00:21:24,880
Wha...?!

293
00:21:25,540 --> 00:21:27,000
Hey! You bastard!

294
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:28,640
Wh-What is this?!

295
00:21:32,900 --> 00:21:35,450
Wh-What are you doing?

296
00:21:35,450 --> 00:21:36,580
Gajeel...

297
00:21:37,950 --> 00:21:41,380
I've totally gotta pay you 
back for lookin' down on us.

298
00:21:45,650 --> 00:21:47,630
I can take both of you on by myself.

299
00:21:48,010 --> 00:21:49,780
Go ahead, attack me at the same time!

300
00:21:51,030 --> 00:21:55,370
Oh, boy! Now Natsu Dragneel of Fairy Tail

301
00:21:55,370 --> 00:21:58,990
is challenging the two of them to a battle!

302
00:22:00,220 --> 00:22:02,160
You're fired up, ain'tcha?

303
00:23:33,790 --> 00:23:36,770
You'll pay for this, Salamander!

304
00:23:37,670 --> 00:23:40,590
I swear, later...

305
00:23:55,860 --> 00:23:57,890
Natsu, I trust you!

306
00:23:57,890 --> 00:23:59,370
Leave it to me. Keep believin'!

307
00:23:59,370 --> 00:24:01,330
You'd never betray me, would you?

308
00:24:01,330 --> 00:24:03,790
I thought this was about 
the match... Of course not!

309
00:24:03,790 --> 00:24:06,510
Natsu, you'd never do anything 
to make me sad, right?!

310
00:24:06,510 --> 00:24:08,500
I wouldn't let anybody make you sad, Happy!

311
00:24:08,500 --> 00:24:13,470
Listen... Somebody ate my fish!

312
00:24:13,970 --> 00:24:16,510
Next time: Natsu vs. the Twin Dragons!

313
00:24:17,190 --> 00:24:18,680
Happy... You gotta believe me...

314
00:24:18,920 --> 00:24:19,830
Natsu...

315
00:24:19,830 --> 00:24:22,750
I-I didn't know it was yours, Happy!

316
00:24:22,750 --> 00:24:24,520
Natsu!

